### 3. Silent Failure Modes

**What could cause this plan to fail silently (bugs not caught by tests)?**

- [ ] Data edge cases not covered by test fixtures
- [ ] Race conditions in async code
- [ ] External service behavior changes
- [ ] Configuration drift between environments
- [ ] Caching layer bypass (code fetches data directly, skipping cache)
- [ ] External API quirks not documented (rate limits, unusual null values, format changes)
- [ ] Test config interfering with feature tests (isolated concerns not isolated)
- [ ] Mock return types not matching real implementations
- [ ] Unreachable code (return statements above initialization)
- [ ] **Incomplete wiring**: Config/interface parameter added but not passed through at ALL instantiation points
- [ ] **Flow path divergence**: New feature wired into one code path but not others (e.g., CLI vs API vs background job)
